.TH "err_pos" 9 "err_pos" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
err_pos \- find the position of a string within a command for error careting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" err_pos
.BI "(char *cmd "  ","
.BI "const char *str "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmd" 12
The tracing command that caused the error
.IP "str" 12
The string to position the caret at within \fIcmd\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Finds the position of the first occurence of \fIstr\fP within \fIcmd\fP.  The
return value can be passed to \fBtracing_log_err\fP for caret placement
within \fIcmd\fP.

Returns the index within \fIcmd\fP of the first occurence of \fIstr\fP or 0
if \fIstr\fP was not found.
